Product name: Vintage Fishbone Lollapalooza 1993 Concert T  FREE SHIPPING
Description:
Great Vintage Fishbone T shirt from the 1993 Lollapalooza Tour,  what an awesome show, with other great bands like Concrete Blond, who didn't last.
  Fishbone was formed in L.A. in 1979 as an Alternative Rock Fusion band.  Original members John Norwood Fisher on bass, and his brother Phillip "Fish" Fisher on drums along with Angelo Moore, also known
as "Dr. Madd Vibe" doing vocals, sax, and theramin, Kendall Jones on guitar, "Dirty" Walter Kibby II vocals and trumpet. Christopher Dowd,  who used the pseudonym "Charlie Down" was on keyboards, trombone,and vocals.   John Norwood Fisher, Angelo Moore and 
and Kibby still exist in today's 2014 Fishbone.  
Although Fishbone had a cult following established in the L.A. area clubs, and were  signed by such giants as Sony, they never acheived superstardom but continue to have a faithful following.  They are termed ska, punk, fusion, alternative, hard rockand soul.  Their varied identifiers may be the reason why, hard to pin down but -they don't care!  
With the Monkey as the Sun,  "Center of the Universe"  - at least, our Universe- he shines brightly as the focal point, on the blackness of space background- with planets, stars, and comets, and moon  swirling  by.  And don't miss the Fishbone logo on the bottom R, of the
front-  fish skeleton in a half darkened planet, guess it's the moon.  Saturn floats on the lower hem as well. 
  This T shirt was mine, only one owner and not worn much as only to yoga occasionally as it's really too big for me.  More like a knee length shirt on me.  
Fishbone's 1993 Album was titled that:  Give a Monkey a Brain and He'll Swear He's the Center of the Universe.

Product name: india shriners fez hat
Description:
red india shriners of Oklahoma City hat with emblem.
made of wool.
hat band made of leather.
made by Craddock Uniforms of Kansas City, MO.
Tag reads size 7 3/8 
*Please note that the hat band has come off the seam.*
India Shriners of Oklahoma City was chartered in 1894 – not long after the parent organization was founded. The history of the Shriners goes back to the 1870s when a group of Masons gathered frequently for lunch at the Knickerbocker Cottage on Sixth Avenue in New York City. A particularly fun-loving group of men who gathered regularly for lunch. The group frequently talked about starting a new fraternity for Masons – one centered on fun and fellowship, more than ritual.
One of the founding members had been to France, and had been invited to a party given by an Arabian diplomat. The exotic style, flavors and music of the Arabian-themed party inspired him to suggest this as a theme for the new fraternity. The group drafted the ritual, designed the emblem and costumes, formulated a salutation and declared that members would wear the red fez, the hat synonymous with the Shriners today.

Product name: Organic Kombucha SCOBY kombucha culture "Scoby / Mushroom" fresh with strong starter tea. Includes directions! Make your own kombucha
Description:
*****If you purchase 3 SCOBYs I’ll give you a fourth SCOBY free ***
I'm an avid home Kombucha brewer; we sell our Kombucha locally.  (If you happen to live between Central Pennsylvania and Philadelphia and are interested in Kombucha, please contact me - we deliver to your doorstep) 
Included in our carefully packaged starter kit is:
-One live, organic, health SCOBY (Symbiotic Colony of Bacteria and Yeast) 3 to 4 inches in diameter
-½ cup of starter tea
-Instructions on how to make your own Kumbucha
-I am passionate about Kombucha and will be more than happy to answer any questions you have along your brewing process.  
We only use organic ingredients – organic sugar, organic tea and non-fluorinated chlorine-free structured water.  
We grow our SCOBYs in glass containers.
All SCOBYs look a little different – each SCOBY will be about 3 to 4 inches in diameter.  The pictures of the SCOBYs are our ‘perfect’ looking ones.  All healthy organic SCOBYs work just the same whether perfect looking or ‘ugly.’ 
One 3 to 4 inch SCOBY is enough if you plan to brew ½ gallon.
If you are going to brew a gallon container I’d recommend 2 of our SCOBYs and if a 2 gallon container I’d recommend 4. 
Some sellers say one SCOBY is enough for a 2 gallon container, but most costumers find it takes a really long time to brew Kombucha if you start with only one SCOBY.
 
 *****If you purchase 3 I’ll give you a fourth one free ***
As SCOBY’s are perishable, we only ship on Monday and Tuesdays to make sure they aren’t stuck in the mail over the weekend.
Kombucha is an ancient fermented, probiotic tea beverage. Kombucha has been revered as a healing tonic for millennia. It is believed to provide healthful micronutrients and bacteria beneficial to digestion, detoxification and immunity. Worldwide, people make and drink kombucha for the way it makes them feel, alive, healed and replenished.
Ancient Chinese called it the “Immortal Health Elixir". Kombucha has been around for more than 2,000 years and has a rich history of health benefits like preventing and fighting cancer, arthritis, and other degenerative diseases. In the first half of the 20th century, extensive scientific research was done on Kombucha’s health benefits in Russia and Germany, mostly because of a push to find a cure for rising cancer rates. Russian scientists discovered that entire regions of their vast country were seemingly immune to cancer and hypothesized that the kombucha, called “tea kvass” there, was the cause. So, they began a series of experiments which not only verified the hypothesis, but began to pinpoint exactly what it is within kombucha which was so beneficial.
Some of Kombucha health benefits:
- liver detoxification
- improved pancreas function
- increased energy
- better digestion
- improved mood (helps with anxiety/depression)
- kills Candida (yeast)
- helps nutrient assimilation
- weight loss
